2020-02-29 11:04:50		list, add or remove IRC servers
2020-02-29 11:04:50		    list: list servers (without argument, this list is displayed)
2020-02-29 11:04:50		listfull: list servers with detailed info for each server
2020-02-29 11:04:50		     add: add a new server
2020-02-29 11:04:50		    name: server name, for internal and display use; this name is used to connect to the server (/connect name) and to set server options: irc.server.name.xxx
2020-02-29 11:04:50		hostname: name or IP address of server, with optional port (default: 6667), many addresses can be separated by a comma
2020-02-29 11:04:50		   -temp: add a temporary server (not saved)
2020-02-29 11:04:50		  option: set option for server (for boolean option, value can be omitted)
2020-02-29 11:04:50		nooption: set boolean option to 'off' (for example: -nossl)
2020-02-29 11:04:50		    copy: duplicate a server
2020-02-29 11:04:50		  rename: rename a server
2020-02-29 11:04:50		 reorder: reorder list of servers
2020-02-29 11:04:50		    open: open the server buffer without connecting
2020-02-29 11:04:50		    keep: keep server in config file (for temporary servers only)
2020-02-29 11:04:50		     del: delete a server
2020-02-29 11:04:50		 deloutq: delete messages out queue for all servers (all messages WeeChat is currently sending)
2020-02-29 11:04:50		    jump: jump to server buffer
2020-02-29 11:04:50		     raw: open buffer with raw IRC data
2020-02-29 11:04:50		  filter: set a new filter to see only matching messages (this filter can be used as input in raw IRC data buffer as well); allowed formats are:
2020-02-29 11:04:50		            *       show all messages (no filter)
2020-02-29 11:04:50		            xxx     show only messages containing "xxx"
2020-02-29 11:04:50		            s:xxx   show only messages for server "xxx"
2020-02-29 11:04:50		            f:xxx   show only messages with a flag: recv (message received), sent (message sent), modified (message modified by a modifier), redirected (message redirected)
2020-02-29 11:04:50		            m:xxx   show only IRC command "xxx"
2020-02-29 11:04:50		            c:xxx   show only messages matching the evaluated condition "xxx", using following variables: output of function irc_message_parse (like nick, command, channel, text, etc., see function info_get_hashtable in plugin API reference for the list of all variables), date (format: "yyyy-mm-dd hh:mm:ss"), server, recv, sent, modified, redirected
2020-02-29 11:04:50		Examples:
2020-02-29 11:04:50		  /server listfull
2020-02-29 11:04:50		  /server add freenode chat.freenode.net
